Aim:

To maintain the Pinnacle Club memberâ€™s information using a Singly Linked List (SLL) and perform:

a) Deletion of the President and Secretary

b) Counting total number of members

c) Displaying all members

Algorithm
1ï¸âƒ£ Start
2ï¸âƒ£ Define Structure:

Define a node structure with:

PRN â†’ student roll number

Name â†’ student name

next â†’ pointer to next node

3ï¸âƒ£ Initialize Linked List:

Set head = NULL (empty list).

4ï¸âƒ£ Function to Delete President:

Function: deletePresident()

If the list is empty (head == NULL):
â†’ Print â€œList is empty, no president to delete.â€

Else:

Create a temporary pointer temp = head

Move head to next node â†’ head = head->next

Delete temp

Print â€œPresident removed successfully.â€

5ï¸âƒ£ Function to Delete Secretary:

Function: deleteSecretary()

If the list is empty (head == NULL):
â†’ Print â€œList is empty, no secretary to delete.â€

Else if the list has only one node (only president):

Delete that node

Set head = NULL

Print â€œSecretary removed (list now empty).â€

Else:

Create two pointers:
temp = head, prev = NULL

Traverse until temp->next == NULL (reaches last node)

The temp node is secretary, and prev is second last node

Set prev->next = NULL

Delete temp

Print â€œSecretary removed successfully.â€

6ï¸âƒ£ Function to Count Total Members:

Function: countMembers()

Initialize count = 0

Set temp = head

While temp != NULL:

Increment count

Move to next node â†’ temp = temp->next

Display total member count.

7ï¸âƒ£ Function to Display All Members:

Function: displayList()

If list is empty â†’ Print â€œNo members in the club.â€

Else:

Set temp = head

Traverse through the list:

If node is first â†’ print â€œPresident: PRN, Nameâ€

If node is last â†’ print â€œSecretary: PRN, Nameâ€

Else â†’ print â€œMember: PRN, Nameâ€

Move temp to next node until end of list.

8ï¸âƒ£ Stop
